OL,8,Fthey have left behind children,
OL,9,Fgrandchildren and great grandchildren
OL,10,Fand many other family members and
OL,11,Ffriends - they lived good and
OL,12,Ffulfilling lives, finding comfort in
OL,13,Ftheir religion. They were on their way
OL,14,Fhome from Tuesday 2 o'clock club,
OL,15,Fwhere they socialised with each other
OL,16,Fand their many friends."JThe judge
OL,17,Fsaid that Ms Cunningham and Ms Foulds
OL,18,Fhad left their loved ones with "many
OL,19,Ffond memories and great joy", but
OL,20,Fadded: "Tragically, that joy has been
OL,21,Freplaced by sorrow and a feeling of
OL,22,Fbeing cheated of their presence at
OL,23,Ffamily events which will now feel
OL,24,Fempty. All of that is your
OL,25,Fresponsibility, Glyn Jones.J"You made
OL,26,Fthe selfish and grossly irresponsible
